title: Google\Cloud\Dlp\V2\TransformationDetails
name: TransformationDetails
description:
Details about a single transformation. This object contains a description of the transformation, information about whether the transformation was successfully applied, and the precise location where the transformation occurred. These details are stored in a user-specified BigQuery table.

Generated from protobuf message google.privacy.dlp.v2.TransformationDetails

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.resource_name
params.description: The name of the job that completed the transformation.

params.name: data.container_name
params.description: The top level name of the container where the transformation is located (this will be the source file name or table name).

params.name: data.transformation
params.description: Description of transformation. This would only contain more than one element if there were multiple matching transformations and which one to apply was ambiguous. Not set for states that contain no transformation, currently only state that contains no transformation is TransformationResultStateType.METADATA_UNRETRIEVABLE.

params.name: data.status_details
params.description: Status of the transformation, if transformation was not successful, this will specify what caused it to fail, otherwise it will show that the transformation was successful.

params.name: data.transformed_bytes
params.description: The number of bytes that were transformed. If transformation was unsuccessful or did not take place because there was no content to transform, this will be zero.

params.name: data.transformation_location
params.description: The precise location of the transformed content in the original container.
